-- FACTBOX: People charged in Galleon insider trading case
-- 
-- Fri Oct 16, 2009 6:24pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/10/16/us-hedgefunds-insidertrading-people-fact-idUSTRE59F5B520091016

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Galleon Group founder Raj Rajaratnam and five others were charged with engaging in the largest ever hedge fund insider-trading scheme, generating profits of more than $20 million over several years, U.S. prosecutors, the FBI and the SEC said Friday. 

 The following describes the main people involved in the case: RAJ RAJARATNAM is founder and manager of multi-billion dollar New York hedge fund complex Galleon. He is the portfolio manager of the Galleon Technology funds. Previously he worked as a registered broker dealer. He is 52 years old and lives in New York city. He has a degree from the University of Sussex, England and an MBA from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania. RAJIV GOEL is a managing director at Intel Capital, which makes proprietary investments in technology companies for Intel. He is friends with Rajaratnam and also received an MBA from Wharton around 1983. He is 51 years old and lives in Los Altos, California. ANIL KUMAR is a director at consulting firm McKinsey and is on the executive board of the Indian School of Business. He is a friend of Rajaratnam's and a direct or indirect investor in certain Galleon funds. He is also 51 and lives in Saratoga, California. DANIELLE CHIESI is a portfolio manager at New Castle, a hedge fund investment adviser based in White Plains, New York that was formerly part of Bear Stearns Asset Management. Chiesi is 43 and lives in New York city. MARK KURLAND is a senior director and general partner at New Castle as well. He is 60 and lives in Mount Kisko, New York. ROBERT MOFFAT is a senior executive at IBM and currently is senior vice president and group executive of the systems and technology group at IBM. He is friends with Chiesi. According to the IBM website, he has worked at the company since 1978. He is a member of the IBM Performance Team and the Corporate Operations Team. He is 53 and lives in Ridgefield, Connecticut.